<div xmlns:perseus="http://www.perseus.org/meta/perseus.rdfs#" xmlns:dctype="http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/" xmlns:tufts="http://www.tufts.edu/" xmlns:alph="http://alpheios.net/namespaces/tei" class="alpheios-lex-text_container en">
    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1914" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βουλή</span></b> : (1) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">counsel,
            plan, decree;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βουλὴ δὲ κακὴ νί̄κησεν ἑταίρων,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 10.46</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> Διὸς
            δ᾽ ἐτελείετο βουλή</span>, the ‘will’ of Zeus, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.5</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; οὔ τοι ἄνευ θεοῦ ἥδε γε βουλή</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.372</span></i>, also in plural.—(2) the
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">council</span> of nobles or elders, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γερόντων,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 2.53</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> 194,
            202</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 3.127</span></i>,
          distinguished from the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγορά</span>, or
          assembly.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
    <div class="alpheios-lex-alph-source">From <u>
            <u>A Homeric Dictionary</u>
        </u> (Georg Autenrieth, New York, Harper and Brothers, 1891) </div>
